OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FDrinking water 'forever    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fchemical' level set too    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fhigh, say scientists       
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Scientists are concerned that the      
OL,6, allowable levels of toxic PFAS "forever
OL,7, chemicals" in UK drinking water are too
OL,8, high.                                  
OL,10,FA BBC study found PFAS levels exceeded 
OL,11,FEuropean safety levels in almost half  
OL,12,Fof the samples taken. However, none    
OL,13,Fexceeded the current UK safety level.  
OL,15,FThe chemicals are in many products such
OL,16,Fas non-stick pans, food packaging,     
OL,17,Fcarpets, furniture, firefighting foam. 
OL,19,FThey have been linked to a range of    
OL,20,Fdiseases, including cancer.            
